    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1798</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3099. Your 2233, 6th. Foreign Office informs me that after giving due
                    consideration to all circumstances, British Government are of opinion that any
                    neutral exporter who entered into a contract after March 1 for export goods from
                    Germany or Austria, did so in full knowledge that something in nature of a
                    blockade was going to be declared by British and French Governments and was
                    therefore acting in hope of being able to ship the goods before the actual
                    declaration. British Government regret therefore their inability to extend
                    exceptionally favorable treatment to applicants in respect of goods ordered or
                    contracted for after March 1, last.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
